Date: 25 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Singapore - Ministry of Health 25 Apr 2003 [edited]
<http://app.moh.gov.sg/sar/sar0301.asp?id=1&mid=6540>

SARS situation update 25 Apr 2003
---------------------------------
As of 25 Apr 2003, 50 SARS patients remain in hospital. There are 3
additional SARS cases reported today. The 3 additional cases are:
(a) 35 year old man who is the son of the 72 year old vegetable seller at
Pasir Panjang Wholesale Market. He had been admitted to Tan Tock Seng
Hospital (TTSH) on 18 Apr 2003 as a suspect SARS case and developed lung
changes yesterday;
(b) 18 month old granddaughter of the 72 year old vegetable seller; she had
been admitted to TTSH on 21 Apr 2003 as a suspect SARS case;
(c) 56 year old woman who is a friend of a probable SARS case; she was
admitted to TTSH on 23 Apr 2003.
Update of Pasir Panjang Wholesale Market (PPWM)
As of today, 8 more suspect cases related to the PPWM have been discharged.
They consist of 1 family contact and 7 visitors. Another 6 people who
visited PPWM were admitted to TTSH as suspects today. There are currently
10 suspect cases admitted in relation to PPWM. They consist of 1 worker and
9 visitors to the market.
A summary of the SARS cases to date:
Discharged: 126 (6 new discharges)
Hospitalised: 50 (including 19 in intensive care)
Deaths: 17 + 2(pending further postmortem test results)
Total: 195
Suspected: 99 (including 7 children under 18 years)
Under home quarantine orders: 2729
(1825 related to PPWM)
